text: Priscilla Lane (June 12, 1915 - April 4, 1995) was an American actress. She acted mostly in movies. She played a heroine in The Roaring Twenties (1939). She played a bride in the movie Arsenic and Old Lace. Lane was born in Indianola, Iowa. Category:Actors from Iowa Category:American movie actors Category:1915 births Category:1995 deaths
title: Priscilla Lane
